%folioinfo \msM\ breaks off, f. 24 missing?
<TEXT> etenaiva tu bandhena baddhāḥ varṇāśramāḥ sadā||</TEXT> 13:8
        <NOTE>The three categories of Łprākṛta$- Łvaikṛta$- and Łdakṣiṇābandha$ appear in commentaries on
              Sāṃkhya texts. One brief explanation that is close to what could be implied 
              here in the \VSS\ is Māṭhatavṛtti ad Sāṃkhyakārikā 44:
                Łtenājñānena manuṣyatiryagdeveṣv ātmānaṃ nibadhnāti | na mokṣaṃ
                gacchatīty arthaḥ | ato 'jñānaṃ nimittaṃ bandho naimittikāḥ | sa ca bandhas
                trividhaḥ | prakṛtibandho vaikārikabandho dakṣiṇābandhaś ceti | tatra
                prakṛtibandho nāmāṣṭāsu prakṛtiṣu paratvenābhimānaḥ | vaikārikabandho nāma
                brahmādisthāneṣu śreyobuddhiḥ | dakṣiṇābandho nāma gavādidānejyānimittaḥ |$ </NOTE>
        <TR>are bound forever by [1] natural (Łprākṛta$), and [2] modified (Łvaikṛta$) bondage, and
                [3] the bondage of ritual reward (Łdakṣiṇā\-bandha$).</TR>

